27/01/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivo Sanader sent a letter of protest to Serbia on Thursday (26 January) following an attack on two embassy personnel in Belgrade Wednesday night. Deputy Ambassador Branimir Loncar and Boris Herceg, first secretary of the embassy's political department, were in a car in a residential district when a window was smashed, injuring Herceg. In a statement to Croatian Foreign Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic, Serbia-Montenegro counterpart Vuk Draskovic condemned the attack and said police are searching for those responsible. (Vjesnik - 27/01/06; HTR, B92 - 26/01/06) 
